link:labelLink.link:label: Financial Performance 1
Expense Electricity Other Than Resale Amount
The cost of acquiring, by payment of money or its equivalent, electricity other than purchases of electricity for resale.
Expense Electricity Renewable Sources Percent
The percentage of purchases of electricity, other than purchases of electricity for resale, which was from renewable sources.
Expense Fuels And Gas Other Than For Resale Amount
Expenditure on fuels and gas other than for the purpose of resale and to power registered transport and motor vehicles.
Expense Other Businesses Excluding Internal Outward Freight And Cartage Amount
Payments to contractors and other businesses for all freight and cartage expenses except for outward and internal freight, cartage, delivery and transport expenses.
This excludes overseas freight and cartage on goods exported.
Expense Other Businesses For Air Emissions Management Amount

Payments to contractors and other businesses for air emissions management.
Air emissions management refers to the construction, maintenance or operation of facilities aimed at the reduction or control of emissions including odours, into the ambient air.
This excludes measures taken for employee health and safety.
Expense Other Businesses For Internal Freight And Cartage Amount

Payments to contractors and other businesses for internal freight, cartage, delivery and transport services where goods are moved. Internal refers to the movement of goods between different locations of this business.
This excludes overseas freight and cartage on goods exported.
Expense Other Businesses For Internal Freight And Cartage Including Postal And Courier Amount

Payments to contractors and other businesses for internal freight, cartage, delivery and transport services where goods are moved. This includes postal and courier expenses. Internal refers to the movement of goods between different locations of this business.
This excludes overseas freight and cartage on goods exported.
Expense Other Businesses For Outward Freight And Cartage Amount
Payments to contractors and other businesses for outward freight, cartage, delivery and transport services where goods are moved. Outward refers to movement of goods sold to customers.
This excludes overseas freight and cartage on goods exported.
Expense Other Businesses For Outward Freight And Cartage Including Postal And Courier Amount

Payments to contractors and other businesses for outward freight, cartage, delivery and transport services where goods are moved. This includes postal and courier expenses. Outward refers to movement of goods sold to customers.
This excludes overseas freight and cartage on goods exported.
Expense Other Businesses For Waste Management Amount
Payments to contractors and other businesses for the provision of waste management services including collection, transportation, recycling, treatment, processing and disposal.
This excludes payments for sewage or drainage management and payments for air emissions management.
Expense Other Businesses For Waste Management Non Recyclables Percent

The percentage of payments to contractors and other businesses for waste management services which were for non-recyclable waste. Waste management services includes the collection, transportation, recycling, treatment, processing and disposal of waste.
Non-recyclable waste is generally defined as any material that once used, cannot be processed into new, potentially useful material.
This excludes payments for sewage or drainage management and payments for air emissions management.
Expense Other Businesses For Waste Management Recyclables Percent

The percentage of payments to contractors and other businesses for waste management services which were for recyclables including green waste. Waste management services includes the collection, transportation, recycling, treatment, processing and disposal of waste.
Recyclable waste is defined as waste that can be recovered through processing to produce material with further usage value.
This excludes payments for sewage or drainage management and payments for air emissions management.
Expense Other Businesses Freight And Cartage Including Postal And Courier Excluding Internal Outward Amount

Payments to contractors and other businesses for all freight and cartage expenses except for outward and internal freight, cartage, delivery and transport expenses. This includes postal and courier expenses.
This excludes overseas freight and cartage on goods exported.
Expense Postal And Courier Services Amount

Expenditure on postal, mailing and courier services. Postal, mail and courier services are the expenses incurred for the pick-up, transport and domestic or international delivery of addressed or unaddressed mail, packages and parcels.
Expense Self Sourced Water License Fees Amount
The expenditure on water license fees and other administration fees for self-sourced water.
Expense Water Other Than Resale Amount
Expenditure on water other than for resale. It excludes expenditure on self-sourced water.
Expense Water Reuse Amount

The amount paid for reuse water excluding purchases of reuse water for resale.
Reuse water is drainage, wastewater or stormwater that has been delivered to this business by another business with or without prior treatment.
Income Delivery Charges Amount
Delivery charges refer to the amount of expense entailed in making a delivery of goods sold by the business.
This excludes delivery charges not separately invoiced or itemised to customers.
Income Delivery Charges Undertaken By Other Businesses Percent
The percentage of delivery charges separately invoiced or itemised to customers for goods sold by this business, where the deliveries were undertaken by other businesses.
Income Delivery Charges Undertaken By This Business Percent
The percentage of delivery charges separately invoiced or itemised to customers for goods sold by this business, where the deliveries were undertaken by vehicles owned or leased by this business.
Income Transport Services By Other Freight Transportation Amount

The income received from transporting goods, where the business has not sold the goods, or owned the goods. It has just provided the transport of the goods via modes of transportation other than road freight transportation.
This excludes freight forwarding services income.
Income Transport Services By Road Freight Transportation Amount
The income received from transporting goods, where the business has not sold the goods, or owned the goods. It has just provided the transport of the goods via road freight transport.
Income Transport Services Goods Not Owned Or Sold Amount
Income received from transporting goods, where the business has not sold or owned the goods. It has just provided the transport of the goods.
Income Transport Services Other Transport Of Goods Amount
All income from the provision of transport services other than from the transportation of goods.
Income Waste Management Services Amount
The income received for the provisions of waste management services in the form of collection, transport, recycling, processing and disposal of waste.
This excludes the treatment, processing or disposal of waste at sewage treatment plants.
Income Waste Management Services Non Recyclables Percent

The percentage of income received for the provision of waste management services which were for non-recyclable waste.
Waste management services include the collection, transport, recycling, processing and disposal of waste. Non-recyclable waste is generally defined as any material that once used, cannot be processed into new, potentially useful material.
This excludes the treatment, processing or disposal of waste at sewage treatment plants.
Income Waste Management Services Recyclables Percent

The percentage of income received from the provision of waste management services which were for recyclables including green waste.
Waste Management services include the collection, transport, recycling, processing and disposal of waste. Recyclable waste is defined as waste that can be recovered through processing to produce material with further usage value.
